icient, equitable, and responsive to the needs of diverse populations.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-62_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-63_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-64_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-66_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-67_ pf-text-1">The health and social care sector in the UK employs over 3 million people, making it one of the largest sectors in the economy.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-69_ pf-text-1">An estimated one in three people in the UK will benefit from social care services at some point in their life.</li></ul><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-71_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These figures underscore the vast scope of health and social care services and the critical need for stringent policy frameworks to guide them.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-73_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Unlocking_Wales_Care_Regulation_Standards_with_ComplyPlus_Solutions_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1712145319" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Unlocking_Wales_Care_Regulation_Standards_with_ComplyPlus_Solutions_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1712145319 1536w" width="2149" height="1637" alt="Revolutionise Your Compliance with ComplyPlus™: The Leading Health and Social Care Policy Management System - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Revolutionise Your Compliance with Comp